## DURING-WRITING PHASE: SECTION 5.7 (Implementation Roadmap)

### 5.7 Checklist:

#### Phase 1 (Immediate, 0-2 weeks):
- [ ] Task 1: Finalize ABC classification (state thresholds explicitly)
- [ ] Task 2: Compute safety stock formulas per quadrant (Q1: 40%, Q2: 10%, Q3: 5%, Q4: 50%)
- [ ] Task 3: Identify top 10 slow movers (DSLS > 90 days) and clearance protocol

#### Phase 2 (Routine, Weeks 2-8):
- [ ] Weekly: Monitor stockout frequency
- [ ] Bi-weekly: Review margin performance
- [ ] Monthly: Re-compute ABC classification

#### Phase 3 (Strategic, Weeks 8-12):
- [ ] Quarterly ABC rebalancing
- [ ] Dynamic pricing pilots (target: 15% margin improvement on low-margin Class A)
- [ ] SKU rationalization (discontinue Q4 products)

#### Success Metrics (≥5 metrics with baseline/target):
- [ ] Revenue CV: Baseline 47% → Target <40%
- [ ] Class A Stockout Rate: Unknown → Target <2%
- [ ] Low-Margin Products: 48% of SKUs → <35% of SKUs
- [ ] Slow-Mover Inventory Value: ₹[X] → <₹[X/2]
- [ ] Price Consistency (Avg CV): 18% → <12%

**Total 5.7 Word Count Target: 250-300 words**

