## TONE & LANGUAGE GUARDRAILS

### Throughout Section 5, Verify:

✓ **Third-Person Professional:**
- [ ] NO "I analyzed" or "we considered" ← change to "Analysis employed" or "Methods selected"
- [ ] NO "I think" or "we believe" ← change to "Evidence suggests" or "Findings indicate"

✓ **Active Voice (Science Writing Standard):**
- [ ] Preferred: "Coefficient of Variation was computed to quantify..."
- [ ] Avoid: "We computed Coefficient of Variation..."

✓ **Quantified Statements:**
- [ ] Every assertion backed by number
- [ ] NO "High volatility" → YES "CV 47% indicates significant demand fluctuation"
- [ ] NO "Some products have low margins" → YES "42 of 87 SKUs (48%) exhibit margins <15%"

✓ **Academic-Professional Phrasing:**
- [ ] "This approach enables..." (vs. "This helps...")
- [ ] "Operationalize the principle..." (vs. "Use the principle...")
- [ ] "Statistically appropriate for..." (vs. "Better for...")

